    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Give and Take on Napster</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Gene Santagada letter says June 29 article on Napster failed to mention that real-time computer-to-computer file exchanges have been popular for years among users of Internet Relay Chat</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>''Napster Rocks the Web'' (State of the Art, June 29) did not mention that real-time computer-to-computer file exchanges have been popular for years among users of Internet Relay Chat.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>''Napster Rocks the Web'' (State of the Art, June 29) did not mention that real-time computer-to-computer file exchanges have been popular for years among users of Internet Relay Chat.</p>
        <p>Besides channels for chatting, there are channels devoted to images, music and particular artists or bands. So people can communicate and exchange files.</p>
        <p>GENE SANTAGADA  Newburgh, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
